title: Grateful Dead Live at Kiel Auditorium on 1979-12-09
description: Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Brown Eyed Women, Cassidy, Row Jimmy, Minglewood Blues, Candyman, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Deal Shakedown Street-> Samson & Delilah, High Time-> Easy To Love You, Terrapin Station-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Black Peter-> I Need

reviews.review_text: FAST This recording is quite fast. I tried to use it to patch the tape flips on the sbd and it was not easy to do....cm

My Bad didn't mean to offend anyone it was just an observation my bad just really enjoyed the soundboard stream and this recording pails in comparison that's all this show was truly epic. I did give credit for trying I probably couldn't do much better with out some good recording equipment my hat is off to the up-loader just wish I had the soundboard recording it is amazing and I feel that every Dead Head young and old should have this recording

Colorado If you didn't sound so dismissive and greedy and asked the community nicely to trade or give you this show then you might get it. Insulting individual tapers on their tapes from 30 plus years ago is not the way to make friends here.

What a show! This puts things in perspective! I was 8 years old the time this was going down and I grew up in St. Louis! What I wouldn't give to have been able to be at this show. Thank you so much for posting, I was sleeping the night away while a 14 minute Shakedown Street was rocking my home town!
